Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveSpecialRoute(25.10)                                saveSpecialRoute(25.10)

Name
       saveSpecialRoute - Saves special route information in a file

Syntax
        saveSpecialRoute

       [-help]

       <filename>

       -pre10

       Saves special route information in a file. If the specified filename is
       compressed (with the .gz extension), the file is gzipped.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each saveSpecialRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man saveSpecialRoute

       <filename>
              Specifies  the  name of the output file into which special route
              information to include metal fill is saved. The file is saved in
              the .spr format.

       -pre10 Saves the routing file with an older version.

Related Information
              * addSpecialRoute

              * loadSpecialRoute

              * Power Planning and Routing and Optimizing Metal Density  chap-
                ters in the Innovus User Guide

